== '''otsukare-samadeshita''' ==

Otsukare-samadeshita is the Japanese expression-word meaning "Nice job" or "Good work", usually said to someone or between the members of a group after a difficult task is finally accomplished.

However, the Japanese use of ''otsukare-samadeshita'' is very multidimensional. It can be applied in several situation and the meaning varies according the moment it is used. For example, saying the same ''Otsukare-samadeshita'' can be understood in English as: "Goddamit, we finished this thing!", when doing boring assignments. But, if after receiving the same boring assignment, your boss or teacher says ''otsukare-samadeshita'' to you, he probably means "You like hell? I gave you hell, didn't I?" It can also mean "Way to go, badasses! We rule!!", after winning a sport match, or yet "Although we played much better, those lucky morons still beat us", used by the defeated part of the same match.